<chapter id="chapter-configuration">
  <title>Configuration</title>

  <para>This section explains how to use this library in your project.</para>

  <section>
    <title>Sources</title>

	  <itemizedlist>
		  <listitem>
			  <para>
				  The javascript Assembly dependency
			  </para>
		  </listitem>
		  <listitem>
			  <para>
				  Assembly JAR file
			  </para>
		  </listitem>
		  <listitem>
			  <para>
				  Assembly ZIP file
			  </para>
		  </listitem>
	  </itemizedlist>
  </section>

	<section>
		<title>Usage of the dependency</title>

		<para>
			Create a Web project and add the following to your pom file.
			This will output the needed js file to the selected output directory.
		</para>

		<programlisting>
			<dependency>
				<groupId>org.geomajas.project</groupId>
				<artifactId>geomajas-project-javascript-assembly</artifactId>
				<version>1.0.0-SNAPSHOT</version>
			</dependency>
		</programlisting>

		<programlisting>
			<plugin>
				<groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>
				<artifactId>maven-dependency-plugin</artifactId>
				<executions>
					<execution>
						<id>unpack assembly</id>
						<phase>generate-sources</phase>
						<goals>
							<goal>unpack</goal>
						</goals>
						<configuration>
							<artifactItems>
								<artifactItem>
									<groupId>org.geomajas.project</groupId>
									<artifactId>geomajas-project-javascript-assembly</artifactId>
									<version>1.0.0-SNAPSHOT</version>
									<type>jar</type>
								</artifactItem>
							</artifactItems>
							<excludes>
								**/WEB-INF/**,
								**/META-INF/**,
								**/org/**
							</excludes>
							<outputDirectory>${basedir}/src/main/webapp</outputDirectory>
						</configuration>
					</execution>
				</executions>
			</plugin>
		</programlisting>

	</section>

	<section>
		<title>Usage of the jar file</title>

		<para>
			Copy the jar file to the WEB-INF/lib folder of your web project.
			You only need to include the 'gm/gm.nocache.js' file in your page to make use of the api.
		</para>

	</section>

	<section>
		<title>Usage of the zip file</title>

		<para>
			This package contains and index.html example with the needed js files.
		</para>

	</section>

</chapter>
